Harry Belafonte, a renowned activist and musician, was a powerful voice for change in the United States. He fought for civil rights and human rights, inspiring a generation of young leaders to fight for justice. Belafonte worked alongside Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. and supported organizations like the Student Nonviolent Coordinating Committee and the Southern Christian Leadership Conference. He used his platform on stage and screen to captivate audiences worldwide. Belafonte's vision for America included dignity, equity, and justice for all, and he worked tirelessly to make that vision a reality. The author, who considered Belafonte a dear friend, expresses their condolences to his family and loved ones.